GA  builds on amd64.

rc1 tests pass on amd64, arm64, i386, sparc64.
rc2 tests pass on amd64, sparc64.
GA  tests pass on amd64.

Investigate whether tests can or should be run over TLS.
Needs a dependency on security/tcltls, but naive attempts failed
due to protocol version mismatches when running the tests.

On macppc, tests run badly into swap on my 250M iBook before timing out.
On armv7, the Redis 6 port is broken the same way as Redis 4 and Redis 5.
